Space Fighter Ace:

Space Fighter Ace version 0.0.1 is an "Space Invader" style video game in which you kill enemies or they kill you.
Copyright (C) 2006 Han Dao (wikipediankiba@gmail.com) and contributors.

This readme file is intended only for version 0.0.1 and no later version of this game.
The website of Space Fighter Ace is http://spaceshooter.rubyforge.org and the project page of Space Fighter Ace is http://www.rubyforge.org/projects/spaceshooter

==INSTALLION==

You simply download the game, unzip the file to a desired location, install dependencies if any, and then click on spacefighterace.rb to play the game.

SPECIAL NOTES: For trunk, you will need to get the RbGooey dependency in Dynpet's SVN at http://sourceforge.net/projects/dynpet

All the other dependencies and their website are listed below in the next section.
==DEPENDENCIES==
All version require the Ruby interpreter to run.

The dependency RbGooey will come with all released version of SpaceFighterAce due to the library's inmaturity and the fact it is still in early developments. 

Source file: File name is spacefighterace-source-0.0.1.tar.bz2

As for the dependency, Rubygame: 
rubygame DLL is available only for window-source of SpaceFighterAce. File name is spacefighterace-window-source-0.0.1.tar.bz2

However, for linux and mac users, they need to install Rubygame themselves. So they will just get the spacefighterace-source-0.0.1.tar.bz2

Websites of dependency:

ruby http://ruby-lang.org
rubygame http://rubygame.infogami.com

==Playing==

When playing the game....

Key:

s - to stop motion of the spacecraft
arrow key right - change the motion to move right
arrow key left - change the motion to move left
space - shoot rockets
